7534254.text:
**``Begin the Data Journey``**

Right-Click on the __Begin the Data Journey__ job and select "Run Job".

Once the job has completed, you can verify that the project is added to Kensu, exploring the newly available Project will show 5 Applications and new Data Sources.

The Applications each represent a transformation Job that has been executed as part of this orchestration, and within those Applications, you can observe Data Sources which were consumed or created by that job.  These jobs represent a simplified data journey from raw warehouse records to meeting specific business reporting needs.

This job can be run multiple times without risk to your environment.

*It may take up to 2 minutes to see these changes within Kensu

7534255.text:
**``Catching Sneaky Schema Changes``**

Once you have followed these steps to set up a schema change rule on the  LINE_ITEM_PRODUCT_DATA Data Source within Kensu, double-click on the Mistakes Happen job below and run the job.

This will change the PRODUCT_ID column from a number type to a Varchar.

Will Kensu catch this sneaky maneuver?

7534252.text:
**``Stop Rule Breakers in their tracks!``**

What if rules could do more than simply alert us?

THEY CAN!

Follow these steps to enable a circuit breaker on your PRODUCT_IMPACT_MODEL application whenever the schema change rule is triggered.

Once the circuit breaker has been created, double-click on the Stop_The_Spread job below and run the job once it opens.

7534253.text:
**``NULL Rows not allowed!``**

Once you have followed these steps to set up a Min/Max rule allowing no NULL values for CUSTOMER_CODE on the  LINE_ITEM_METRICS Data Source within Kensu, double-click on the __Absent_Customers__ job below and run the job.

This will cause all values in the CUSTOMER_CODE column to be NULL.

Let's see how the Kensu Platform responds!

7534314.text:
**``Migrate and Transform``**

This Orchestration will run through 5 Transformation Jobs each job will be reflected as an Application within your Kensu Project.  These jobs represent a simplified data journey from raw warehouse records to meeting specific business reporting needs.

Once this job is run, you will be able to observe this journey within Kensu.

7534315.text:
**``Dynamic Starting Point``**

This job will create structures dynamically within Snowflake. Because there is no data movement, this job will not be visible within Kensu but will result in PRODUCT and ORDER_ITEMS tables which will be used as data sources for starting your data pipeline.

This is done so that you can experience Data Observation with Kensu from the safety of a self-contained environment.

7534498.text:
**``NULL Rows not allowed!``**

The component job below is the same __Inventory_Finance_Calculations__ job that populated the LINE_ITEM_METRICS table, but the Component below sets  the **CUST_CODE_BEHAVIOR** variable  to 'BROKEN', 

This variable controls whether customer codes are populated (NORMAL) or NULL (BROKEN).  

Running this job will result in CUSTOMER_CODE being set to NULL in the LINE_ITEM_METRICS table.

Once the job has run, close out of this job and return to the Kensu Platform.

Let's see how the Kensu Platform responds!

1.value:
/* Note: this query will be run as a subquery for the purposes of sampling the data.
   As such it will be restricted by any subquery limitations specified by the current platform. */
   
   
Select CASE 
		WHEN DATA_TYPE = 'TEXT' THEN 'NUMBER'
        WHEN DATA_TYPE = 'NUMBER' THEN 'VARCHAR'
       END "DT"
	From information_schema.columns
where table_catalog = '${environment_database}'
		and table_schema = '${environment_default_schema}'
		and table_name = 'LINE_ITEM_PRODUCT_DATA' 
        and column_name = 	'PRODUCT_ID'

7534482.text:
**``Creating the Problem``**

This executes the same **Product_Inventory** job that created your table; only this time passes in EITHER __VARCHAR__  OR __NUMBER__for the PRODUCT_DATA_TYPE variable that is used to recreate the table.  This job is designed to always change the schema of the LINE_ITEM_PRODUCT_DATA table.

7534483.text:
**``Return a Different Data_Type``**

This queries the information schema of LINE_ITEM_PRODUCT_DATA for the Data_Type of the PRODUCT_ID column and returns __VARCHAR__ when the current data_type is __NUMBER__ and NUMBER when the current data_type is TEXT.  This result updates the variable that is passed into the LINE_ITEM_PRODUCT_DATA job.

7534491.text:
**``Kensu Circuit Breaker``**

This is the Kensu Circuit Breaker shared job which is available [[here.]]

When a ticket is open for a circuit breaker rule referencing your Application, the component will return a failure stating the Kensu Application that triggered the circuit breaker.

Go ahead and run this job while the ticket is open and make sure to read the message in your task panel when the circuit breaker is triggered.

7534381.text:
**PRODUCT_ID Data Type**

This Component converts the data type for the Product_id column, the default value is "NUMBER" but this can be changed by updating the "Product_Data_Type" job variable

1.value:
case when '${CUST_CODE_BEHAVIOR}' = 'BROKEN' then NULL
else CUSTOMER_CODE
end

definition.name: CUST_CODE_BEHAVIOR
definition.description: This variable dictates whether customer codes are populated (NORMAL) or made NULL (BROKEN),

1.value:
SELECT 
  "DATES"."ORDER_DATE" AS "ORDER_DATE" 
FROM (select
  dateadd(day, '-' || seq4(), current_date()) as ORDER_DATE, uniform(1, 13, random())R 
from
  table
    (generator(rowcount => 95))
) AS "DATES" 
     INNER JOIN 
     ((SELECT 
	uniform(1, 13, random())R 
FROM 
	table(generator(rowCount => 550)))
) AS "ROWS" 
     ON "DATES"."R"="ROWS"."R"
     ORDER BY ORDER_DATE
DATEADD(MINUTE, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY ORDER_DATE ORDER BY 1)*13, DATEADD(HOUR, 10, "ORDER_DATE"))
ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY ORDER_ID ORDER BY 1)

CASE
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE < 1 THEN 'UNDER A DOLLAR'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 1 AND 5 THEN '$1 - $5'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 5 AND 10 THEN '$5 - $10'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 10 AND 20 THEN '$10 - $20'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 20 AND 40 THEN '$20 - $40'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 40 AND 60 THEN '$40 - $60'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE BETWEEN 60 AND 100 THEN '$60 - $100'
     WHEN ITEM_PRICE > 100 THEN 'OVER $100'
END

CASE

    WHEN DAYOFMONTH("ORDER_TIMESTAMP") BETWEEN 10 AND 20 THEN 'MIDDLE OF MONTH'
    WHEN DAYOFMONTH("ORDER_TIMESTAMP") > 20 THEN 'END OF MONTH'
